31:43.869 --> 31:45.937 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HOMRAJ ACHARYA: Children, yes,
because, you
know, it's a family-based
industry.

31:45.971 --> 31:53.378 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: They live in
brick shacks,
surrounded by LEGO-like
fortresses, molded

31:53.411 --> 31:58.216 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
bricks stacked up at the start
of an almost
preindustrial process.

31:58.250 --> 32:02.821 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
For brick makers, there are no
set working
hours. The basic rule is, you
work until you're

32:02.854 --> 32:08.059 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
too tired to continue, and
there's every incentive
to continue to the point of
exhaustion, because

32:08.093 --> 32:13.698 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
workers are paid by the brick.
They get a
little less than one U.S. cent
for every one

32:13.732 --> 32:15.500 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
of these that they produce.

32:15.534 --> 32:20.605 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HOMRAJ ACHARYA: Because it's
paid on a piece
basis, so if children are making
like hundred

32:20.639 --> 32:23.742 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
bricks more, so that means you
might get a
hundred.

32:23.775 --> 32:27.279 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: So, they
help the productivity,
which helps their wages?

32:27.312 --> 32:29.114 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
HOMRAJ ACHARYA: Yes, exactly.

32:29.147 --> 32:32.818 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: Do the
children help mold
bricks, I asked the Moktan?
Seven-year-old

32:32.851 --> 32:35.821 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Ritesh, no, but 12-year-old
Ritika, yes.

32:35.854 --> 32:40.759 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
TILOOK MOKTAN (through
translator): She works
a few hours a week. She helps
with the cooking.

32:40.792 --> 32:44.196 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, sometimes, when their
mother needs to
do the cooking, she helps out
with the bricks.

32:44.229 --> 32:48.667 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: It may seem
normal for
children to pitch in with
chores. But Acharya

32:48.700 --> 32:54.439 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
says these desperately poor
families invariably
grow to depend excessively on
the children

32:54.472 --> 32:56.341 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
to scrape together more income.

32:56.374 --> 33:01.713 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HOMRAJ ACHARYA: The system
creates that enabling
environment for children to be
used.

33:01.746 --> 33:06.418 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: The Better
Brick program
wants to create a different
environment, using

33:06.451 --> 33:12.624 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
incentives for kiln owners.

33:12.657 --> 33:17.929 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Those who sign on agree to pay
for preschool
facilities like this one to get
children into

33:17.963 --> 33:23.501 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a classroom and away from the
brick workplace
of their parents. And BBN works
with owners

33:23.535 --> 33:27.572 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and parents to ensure that older
children
attend school.

33:27.606 --> 33:30.108 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
For owners, these steps could be
good business.

33:30.141 --> 33:36.114 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HOMRAJ ACHARYA: Giving them
incentive in terms
of access to loans, and there is
helping them

33:36.147 --> 33:41.553 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to improve their quality of
bricks, and then,
when there is a bidding process,
we are talking

33:41.586 --> 33:43.255 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
to the government.

33:43.288 --> 33:46.358 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: So you would
want the
government to procure bricks,
when it buys

33:46.391 --> 33:52.130 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
bricks, from operators who are
certified as
not employing children and
improving conditions?

33:52.163 --> 33:56.534 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HOMRAJ ACHARYA: Absolutely. Yes,
that is one
of the -- the major point of
this program.

33:56.568 --> 34:02.474 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: This is one
of 23 kilns
that have so far signed on to
the program.

34:02.507 --> 34:08.046 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Co-owner Shiva Regmi said he's
happy to improve
conditions for workers, and he
can certainly

34:08.079 --> 34:09.848 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
use the technical help.

34:09.881 --> 34:13.652 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SHIVA REGMI, Kiln Owner (through
translator):
For every one brick that we
make, two are

34:13.685 --> 34:15.553 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
broken.

34:15.587 --> 34:18.523 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: Regmi is a
newcomer to
this business -- this kiln is
just a few months

34:18.556 --> 34:23.328 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
old -- and he may be more
receptive to the
Better Brick program than
others.

34:23.361 --> 34:28.333 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
At another facility, the owner
complained
to Acharya that his industry is
being unfairly

34:28.366 --> 34:30.302 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
singled out by advocates.

34:30.335 --> 34:35.907 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MAN (through translator): We are
giving opportunities
to 400,000 people who work in
our industry,

34:35.941 --> 34:40.812 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and we don't ask their children
to work. People
are spreading rumors that we are
hiring children,

34:40.845 --> 34:42.681 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
but that's not true.

34:42.714 --> 34:46.451 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: Many owners
can technically
make that claim, Acharya says,
because their

34:46.484 --> 34:53.792 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
contracts are with adults. It's
parents who
press their children into
service.

34:53.825 --> 34:59.097 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Then there's the murkier world
of subcontractors
who provide laborers, many of
them children

34:59.130 --> 35:04.135 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
who are not with their families
brought here
under various arrangements by
labor agents

35:04.169 --> 35:09.507 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
or traffickers. It was quite
common to see
young boys loading and herding
the steady

35:09.541 --> 35:13.678 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
train of work animals that carry
raw bricks
to the kilns.

35:13.712 --> 35:18.149 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It was more difficult to talk to
them. In
a strange twist, children here,
like many

35:18.183 --> 35:24.389 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
other places, are told not to
talk to strangers.
I did manage one fleeting
conversation with

35:24.422 --> 35:26.424 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
this young man.

35:26.458 --> 35:31.696 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
"I had to leave school because
my mom and
dad weren't earning," he said,
"so I went

35:31.730 --> 35:32.564 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
to work."

35:32.597 --> 35:35.800 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
"How did you get this job?" I
asked.

35:35.834 --> 35:38.903 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
"A rich man from our village
brought me here,"
he said.

35:38.937 --> 35:41.773 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
How many others accompanied him?

35:41.806 --> 35:45.543 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
"Oh, there are many," he said.
"All these
guys are from my village."

35:45.577 --> 35:49.514 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
"Do you get any time to play?" I
asked.

35:49.547 --> 35:52.584 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
"I do not play," he said.

35:52.617 --> 35:59.491 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And no more time for a stranger.
His is just
one anonymous story of thousands
in an underground

35:59.524 --> 36:05.864 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
labyrinth that preys on poverty
and illiteracy,
one Nepal's government admits it
has few resources

36:05.897 --> 36:07.699 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
to police.

36:07.732 --> 36:13.872 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But Homraj Acharya sees a tiny
silver lining.
Reconstruction will soon get
into high gear

36:13.905 --> 36:17.409 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
with a windfall of foreign aid.
And, here,
he sees leverage.

36:17.442 --> 36:22.347 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HOMRAJ ACHARYA: Four billion has
already been
pledged by different countries.
And we want

36:22.380 --> 36:28.686 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to make sure that all of those
countries who
are giving money to Nepalese
government do

36:28.720 --> 36:32.924 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
-- we want them to use the
bricks that are
produced child-labor-free.

36:32.957 --> 36:38.196 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: He says
Nepal's builders
association has agreed to buy
bricks from

36:38.229 --> 36:44.335 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
kilns his program has certified
as free of
child labor, where they're
available.

36:44.369 --> 36:49.174 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And it seems more likely the
Moktan family's
bricks will be free of child
labor, especially

36:49.207 --> 36:53.978 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
after our interview, when I
asked sixth-grader
Ritika what her favorite subject
was.

36:54.012 --> 36:55.647 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
GIRL: English.

36:55.680 --> 36:58.450 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: When you
grow up, what
kind of work would you like to
do?

36:58.483 --> 37:02.353 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
GIRL: I would like to be a
doctor.

37:02.387 --> 37:06.257 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: Doctor. Why?

37:06.291 --> 37:09.861 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
GIRL: Because I want to help the
poor people.

37:09.894 --> 37:15.633 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: Two short,
hesitant sentences,
but to her parents, she'd moved
a mountain,

37:15.667 --> 37:17.836 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
and she'd moved them to tears.

37:17.869 --> 37:22.707 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
TILOOK MOKTAN (through
translator): I'm really
proud that she was able to speak
to you in

37:22.740 --> 37:23.942 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
English.

37:23.975 --> 37:25.977 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WOMAN (through translator): They
are tears
of happiness.

37:26.010 --> 37:30.548 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
TILOOK MOKTAN (through
translator): We will
work as hard as we possibly can
to see that

37:30.582 --> 37:32.417 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
she completes her education.

37:32.450 --> 37:36.621 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: For the "PBS
NewsHour,"
this is Fred de Sam Lazaro in
Nepal's Kathmandu

37:36.654 --> 37:38.456 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Valley.

